ex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3614215\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 20, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kto1665702611220.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kto1665702611220.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kto1665702611220.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kto1665702611220\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Gradient Color Start (BackColorStart)\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The \n                                BackColorStart widget property determines the color used at the start of a gradient background in an area frame for entity. The default is <code class=\"ph codeph\">white</code>.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"kto1665702611220__topic_d104342e1_d104343e1_d104344e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kto1665702611220__p_d104345e1_d104346e1_d104347e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>BackColorStart<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">ColorName</var>\n            | <var class=\"keyword varname\">HexColorNumber</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"kto1665702611220__section_w58ab1b5b3_w59ab1b5_w60ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kto1665702611220__p_d104348e1_d104349e1_d104350e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"BackColorStart=#505050\"</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section table\" id=\"kto1665702611220__section_w61ab1b5b5_w62ab1b5_w63ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"kto1665702611220__d5952e17\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kto1665702611220__d5952e17__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kto1665702611220__d5952e17__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kto1665702611220__d5952e17__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">ColorName</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kto1665702611220__d5952e17__entry__2\">Name of a web color or system color. For more\n                        information, see the \"Standard Colors\" topic.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kto1665702611220__d5952e17__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">HexColorNumber</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kto1665702611220__d5952e17__entry__2\">Hexadecimal number (prefixed by a hash mark) of\n                        a color. For example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">#D90E1A</code>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kto1665702611220__d5952e17__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">RGBColor</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kto1665702611220__d5952e17__entry__2\">RGB (Red Green Blue) numeric values in the form\n                           <var class=\"keyword varname\">R</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">G</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">B</var>. For example <code class=\"ph codeph\">255,0,0</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kto1665702611220__section_agt_x1c_xwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d104391e166\">Usage</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"kto1665702611220__table_d12323e1_d12324e1_d12325e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Dynamic?</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Yes for entities, No for area frames</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Supported in Grid?</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">No</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Dependencies:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Applicable only if  BackcolorFill is <code class=\"ph codeph\">gradient</code>.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kto1665702611220__section_y1f_z1c_xwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d104391e217\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kto1665702611220__p_d104357e1_d104358e1_d104359e1\">The \n            BackColorStart enables you to mix two background colors, shading from  BackColorStart into  BackColor.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kto1665702611220__section_enf_1bc_xwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d104391e233\">Example: Setting in ProcScript</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kto1665702611220__p_d104363e1_d104364e1_d104365e1\">For the entities, this property can be set in\n            ProcScript using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$entityProperties</span> or\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$curEntProperties</span> commands.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"kto1665702611220__pre_r2f_cbc_xwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">variables\n string vProperties\nendvariables\nputitem/id vProperties,\"Borderradius\",\"20px\"\nputitem/id vProperties,\"backcolor\",\"darkseagreen\"\nputitem/id vProperties,\"backcolorfill\",\"gradient\"\nputitem/id vProperties,\"gradientstart\",\"bottom\"\nputitem/id vProperties,\"gradientstartcolor\",\"lightblue\"\n$entityproperties(ORDER.SALES)=vProperties</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"kto1665702611220__fig_d104366e1_d104367e1_d104368e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Result</figcaption>\n<br/><img alt=\"Image\" class=\"image\" id=\"kto1665702611220__image_bwf_dbc_xwb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/gradientstartandcolor.png?_LANG=enus\"/><br/>\n</figure>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kto1665702611220__section_cww_dbc_xwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d104391e263\">Example: Setting in Initialization File</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kto1665702611220__p_d104375e1_d104376e1_d104377e1\">For area frames, you can specify this property on\n            the basis of frame names in the [areaframes] section of the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span>.\n            It is not possible to set this property in the Uniface IDE. For more information, see\n            the \"[areaframes]\" topic.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"kto1665702611220__pre_ctr_fbc_xwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[areaframes]\nframe_gradient=uframe(backcolor=red;backcolorfill=gradient;backcolorstart=yellow)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kto1665702611220__section_svx_fbc_xwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d104391e278\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"kto1665702611220__ul_ic3_hbc_xwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kto1665702611220__li_d41444e1_d41445e1_d41446e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ujj1665702610581.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujj1665702610581.html\" title=\"Area frames are objects that can be used to group or separate the contents of a Form component.\">Area Frames and Lines</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kto1665702611220__li_d41447e1_d41448e1_d41449e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iic1718342502908.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iic1718342502908.html\" title=\"The udefentity widget is the default widget for entities in form components. It is a multi-occurrence list, with a minimum of one occurrence, in which fields can be freely arranged. Uniface provides a default logical widget called DefEntity that is mapped to this widget.\">udefentity (Default Entity Widget )</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rcm1665702587635.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Standard Colors</a><p>Uniface supports standard color definitions including system colors as defined by the operating system, Web colors defined by the W3C, and RGB (red-green-blue) colors expressed in hex or decimal numbers. Any of these color definitions can be used when defining the value of foreground and background colors of components, widgets, panels, and toolbars.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sra1665702688552.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>[areaframes]</a><p>The [areaframes] section of the initialization file contains logical widget definitions for frames in Form components.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614215\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614215\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Gradient Color Start (BackColorStart) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 20, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Gradient Color Start (BackColorStart) The BackColorStart widget property determines the color used at the start of a gradient background in an area frame for entity. The default is white . \" BackColorStart = ColorName | HexColorNumber \" Example: \"BackColorStart=#505050\" Value Description ColorName Name of a web color or system color. For more information, see the \"Standard Colors\" topic. HexColorNumber Hexadecimal number (prefixed by a hash mark) of a color. For example: #D90E1A . RGBColor RGB (Red Green Blue) numeric values in the form R , G , B . For example 255,0,0 Usage Dynamic? Yes for entities, No for area frames Supported in Grid? No Dependencies: Applicable only if BackcolorFill is gradient . Description The BackColorStart enables you to mix two background colors, shading from BackColorStart into BackColor. Example: Setting in ProcScript For the entities, this property can be set in ProcScript using the $entityProperties or $curEntProperties commands. variables string vProperties endvariables putitem/id vProperties,\"Borderradius\",\"20px\" putitem/id vProperties,\"backcolor\",\"darkseagreen\" putitem/id vProperties,\"backcolorfill\",\"gradient\" putitem/id vProperties,\"gradientstart\",\"bottom\" putitem/id vProperties,\"gradientstartcolor\",\"lightblue\" $entityproperties(ORDER.SALES)=vProperties Copy Figure 1. Result Example: Setting in Initialization File For area frames, you can specify this property on the basis of frame names in the [areaframes] section of the .ini . It is not possible to set this property in the Uniface IDE. For more information, see the \"[areaframes]\" topic. [areaframes] frame_gradient=uframe(backcolor=red;backcolorfill=gradient;backcolorstart=yellow) Copy Applies To Area Frames and Lines udefentity (Default Entity Widget ) Related Links Standard Colors Uniface supports standard color definitions including system colors as defined by the operating system, Web colors defined by the W3C, and RGB (red-green-blue) colors expressed in hex or decimal numbers. Any of these color definitions can be used when defining the value of foreground and background colors of components, widgets, panels, and toolbars. [areaframes] The [areaframes] section of the initialization file contains logical widget definitions for frames in Form components. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}